00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:00,543
Keep your eyes on the prize.

512
00:43:00,544 --> 00:43:02,878
Find me Simpson. Viper-One, out.

513
00:43:02,879 --> 00:43:05,087
Roger that.

514
00:43:07,818 --> 00:43:10,197
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

515
00:43:13,623 --> 00:43:17,693
Major, how's everything
going out there?

516
00:43:17,694 --> 00:43:19,228
This shithead pushing
up daisies yet?

517
00:43:19,229 --> 00:43:21,163
I'm in the middle of it now.

518
00:43:21,164 --> 00:43:22,631
Gunnery Sergeant Beckett with you?

519
00:43:22,632 --> 00:43:24,333
He's confined to base.

520
00:43:24,334 --> 00:43:25,501
Is he?

521
00:43:25,502 --> 00:43:27,136
<i>That's where I left him.</i>

522
00:43:27,137 --> 00:43:30,643
Well, he's gone. Hasn't
been seen since yesterday.

523
00:43:32,009 --> 00:43:33,979
That's news to me.

524
00:43:34,211 --> 00:43:37,146
I'm starting to get a bad
feeling about this, Major.

525
00:43:37,147 --> 00:43:38,247
Finish it!

526
00:43:38,248 --> 00:43:41,817
So no pressure then. Just hurry up.

527
00:43:41,818 --> 00:43:44,163
Exactly, Major.

528
00:43:44,321 --> 00:43:45,921
No more Marines dying.

529
00:43:45,922 --> 00:43:47,994
Roger that.

530
00:43:57,567 --> 00:44:01,471
Okay, boys. Stay sharp now.

531
00:44:01,505 --> 00:44:04,112
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

532
00:44:11,348 --> 00:44:14,950
Viper-One, Viper-One, got a
second truck at my 10 o'clock.

533
00:44:14,951 --> 00:44:17,296
Roger that, Viper-Two.

534
00:44:30,767 --> 00:44:35,444
Team Alpha, Team Bravo,
get ready to bound.

535
00:44:47,818 --> 00:44:49,788
Let's go.

536
00:45:00,397 --> 00:45:01,764
Team Charlie, you are on me.

537
00:45:01,765 --> 00:45:04,008
We're fire support.

538
00:45:04,968 --> 00:45:07,211
Take that window.

539
00:45:07,471 --> 00:45:09,475
You take that window.

540
00:45:16,413 --> 00:45:18,656
(CHATTERING)

541
00:45:37,601 --> 00:45:39,741
(STATIC OVER RADIO)

542
00:45:45,075 --> 00:45:47,109
Shit. We're made.

543
00:45:47,110 --> 00:45:49,045
Shooter!

544
00:45:49,312 --> 00:45:51,413
Take them! Take them now!

545
00:45:51,414 --> 00:45:53,987
(HEAVY GUNFIRE)

546
00:45:56,019 --> 00:45:58,557
(CLAMORING)

547
00:46:00,957 --> 00:46:02,892
(GRUNTS)

548
00:46:12,869 --> 00:46:14,907
Which way? Which way?

549
00:46:30,987 --> 00:46:32,121
Should we engage?

550
00:46:32,122 --> 00:46:34,557
Protect Shope and look for
Tango. That's our mission.

551
00:46:34,558 --> 00:46:37,199
<i>Keep your head down on that scope.</i>

552
00:46:37,827 --> 00:46:41,765
Advance, advance! Move in!
Cover me! Cover me!

553
00:46:51,641 --> 00:46:53,576
(GRUNTS)

554
00:47:25,242 --> 00:47:28,918
Viper-Two, Viper-Two,
we've got enemy sniper fire.

555
00:47:35,118 --> 00:47:37,759
ATB Tangos, 11 o'clock.

556
00:47:39,856 --> 00:47:41,290
Fuck!

557
00:47:41,291 --> 00:47:44,467
Cantara? Cantara?

558
00:47:49,599 --> 00:47:52,568
Viper-One, Viper-One, this is
Viper-Two. I got a man down!

559
00:47:52,569 --> 00:47:55,537
They've got counter-sniper
support. How copy?

560
00:47:55,538 --> 00:47:57,473
Start shooting.

561
00:48:26,936 --> 00:48:28,270
We're pinned!

562
00:48:28,271 --> 00:48:31,344
We need to change this fucking game!

563
00:48:33,743 --> 00:48:35,678
Gotcha, bitch.

564
00:48:38,348 --> 00:48:40,318
(GRUNTS)

565
00:49:11,481 --> 00:49:13,649
Nice work. That's a game changer.

566
00:49:13,650 --> 00:49:15,756
It wasn't me.

567
00:49:16,186 --> 00:49:18,121
Brandon.

568
00:49:19,222 --> 00:49:21,192
(CLICKING)

569
00:49:22,859 --> 00:49:24,526
Zaim!

570
00:49:24,527 --> 00:49:26,633
Zaim!

571
00:49:31,234 --> 00:49:32,368
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

572
00:49:32,369 --> 00:49:34,475
LIGHT 'EM UP, ZAIM!

573
00:49:35,338 --> 00:49:37,478
LIGHT 'EM UP, ZAIM!

574
00:49:37,741 --> 00:49:39,711
RPG!

575
00:49:49,519 --> 00:49:51,659
(SHOUTING)

576
00:50:08,104 --> 00:50:10,574
(GRUNTS)

577
00:50:19,416 --> 00:50:21,049
- Move in! Move in!
- Hustle! Hustle!

578
00:50:21,050 --> 00:50:25,354
Let's push the perimeter! Fucking
push down, let's go! Move in!

579
00:50:25,355 --> 00:50:27,055
Go!

580
00:50:27,056 --> 00:50:29,091
Move in, rig the truck.

581
00:50:29,092 --> 00:50:30,225
Blow all the merch.

582
00:50:30,226 --> 00:50:32,867
Nothing gets back on the market!

583
00:51:27,016 --> 00:51:28,584
Anybody with me?

584
00:51:28,585 --> 00:51:30,319
<i>SANAA: I'm here.</i>

585
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:32,563
Cantara's gone.

586
00:51:39,762 --> 00:51:43,799
Corporal, you tough it out.

587
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:45,934
This is a high stress event.

588
00:51:45,935 --> 00:51:47,905
It's the job.

589
00:51:48,171 --> 00:51:49,605
SHOPE: Clear!

590
00:51:49,606 --> 00:51:51,640
We're blowing this truck!

591
00:51:51,641 --> 00:51:53,952
Watch your backs!

592
00:51:58,815 --> 00:52:01,149
Well, that was a goat fuck, huh?

593
00:52:01,150 --> 00:52:03,852
Looks like your assassin
didn't get the invitation.

594
00:52:03,853 --> 00:52:05,854
Our Intel says he did!

595
00:52:05,855 --> 00:52:07,856
Yeah, well, your Intel can blow me!

596
00:52:07,857 --> 00:52:11,636
Job's done! Let's get
the fuck outta...

597
00:53:02,045 --> 00:53:04,583
Rookie mistake, Junior.

598
00:53:04,747 --> 00:53:07,449
The air is heavy, the light is low

599
00:53:07,450 --> 00:53:11,354
and you don't got the range
with that 308, do you, kid?

600
00:53:35,979 --> 00:53:38,722
(EXHALES) Sleep tight, kid.

601
00:53:39,582 --> 00:53:41,552
(GROANS)

602
00:54:06,009 --> 00:54:08,013
(GRUNTS)

603
00:54:32,435 --> 00:54:34,871
(DOG BARKING)

604
00:54:39,542 --> 00:54:44,720
<i>MAN: Be advised, be advised, we've
got an unidentified Marine coming in.</i>

605
00:55:05,802 --> 00:55:08,443
Identify yourself.

606
00:55:12,141 --> 00:55:14,976
Thomas Beckett, former
US Marine. Who are you?

607
00:55:14,977 --> 00:55:17,413
What the hell?

608
00:55:18,715 --> 00:55:21,617
The rumor was you were dead,
Master Gunnery Sergeant.

609
00:55:22,752 --> 00:55:25,020
I've been dead before, Major.

610
00:55:25,021 --> 00:55:28,590
Where is Gunnery Sergeant
Brandon Beckett?

611
00:55:28,591 --> 00:55:30,025
I left him back at the base.

612
00:55:30,026 --> 00:55:32,064
Bullshit, he was here.

613
00:55:32,662 --> 00:55:34,666
He's a resourceful kid.

614
00:55:35,565 --> 00:55:38,500
So, this is how you
take care of my son?

615
00:55:38,501 --> 00:55:41,036
Your son is a force recon
Marine Scout Sniper

616
00:55:41,037 --> 00:55:43,905
highly skilled in field
craft and marksmanship.

617
00:55:43,906 --> 00:55:47,676
The Corps has spent a lot of time and
money teaching him how to survive.

618
00:55:47,677 --> 00:55:52,753
Now, are you gonna tell me why
you're on this side of the ground?

619
00:55:53,116 --> 00:55:56,051
- Disappointed?
- A little.

620
00:55:56,052 --> 00:55:58,295
Takes a lot to kill a legend.

621
00:55:58,521 --> 00:56:00,589
If the assassin thought I was dead,

622
00:56:00,590 --> 00:56:03,225
I figured he'd do what you did.

623
00:56:03,226 --> 00:56:04,359
And what would I do?

624
00:56:04,360 --> 00:56:06,261
Go to the next man on the list.

625
00:56:06,262 --> 00:56:10,302
So, who is the sniper?

626
00:56:11,701 --> 00:56:13,902
Army Ranger David Simpson.

627
00:56:13,903 --> 00:56:15,873
Simpson?

628
00:56:16,405 --> 00:56:19,842
(SIGHS) Now that's a damn shame.

629
00:56:20,209 --> 00:56:24,613
I put some lead on him, but he was
too far for me to put his lights out.

630
00:56:25,281 --> 00:56:27,353
Master Guns?

631
00:56:27,884 --> 00:56:30,024
A word.

632
00:56:31,120 --> 00:56:33,294
BECKETT: What's on your mind, Major?

633
00:56:33,823 --> 00:56:39,194
BIDWELL: To say you're a long way
from home is an understatement.

634
00:56:39,796 --> 00:56:42,430
We're in the middle
of the Middle East.

635
00:56:42,431 --> 00:56:45,038
Allah himself doesn't
know that we're here.

636
00:56:45,968 --> 00:56:47,435
So how do you?

637
00:56:47,436 --> 00:56:49,471
I know people, too.

638
00:56:49,472 --> 00:56:52,808
Are we playing on the same team?

639
00:56:52,809 --> 00:56:55,677
I'm playing to keep Brandon
alive, that's my mission.

640
00:56:55,678 --> 00:56:57,746
And to kill Simpson.

641
00:56:57,747 --> 00:57:01,321
My life, nah, my life's been lived.

642
00:57:30,213 --> 00:57:34,890
BIDWELL: Sun will be up in a couple
of hours. We'll find this guy.

643
00:57:39,288 --> 00:57:41,360
Wait.

644
00:57:49,398 --> 00:57:52,642
BECKETT: This blood's fresh.
This was Simpson's hide.

645
00:57:54,070 --> 00:57:55,704
I'll track Brandon and Simpson.

646
00:57:55,705 --> 00:57:57,072
Yeah, we'll come with you.

647
00:57:57,073 --> 00:57:58,740
BECKETT: Negative, Major.

648
00:57:58,741 --> 00:58:00,909
I counted at least
two other combatants

649
00:58:00,910 --> 00:58:02,878
that lived through your
donnybrook and made it out.

650
00:58:02,879 --> 00:58:04,512
They could be working with Simpson.

651
00:58:04,513 --> 00:58:06,481
So you two have to go after them.

652
00:58:06,482 --> 00:58:08,516
I'll go west. I know that terrain.

653
00:58:08,517 --> 00:58:10,051
Yeah, I'll go to the east.

654
00:58:10,052 --> 00:58:13,296
So if this is more than just
Simpson, who are they working for?

655
00:58:14,357 --> 00:58:17,294
We'll ask whoever we leave alive.

656
00:58:17,493 --> 00:58:19,463
Happy hunting.

657
01:01:36,559 --> 01:01:38,631
(GRUNTING)

658
01:02:12,194 --> 01:02:14,266
Drop your fucking gun.

659
01:02:29,512 --> 01:02:32,647
Don't move. Put the weapon down.

660
01:02:32,648 --> 01:02:34,618
I don't have one.

661
01:02:35,718 --> 01:02:37,722
What are you doing?

662
01:02:38,621 --> 01:02:40,955
I'm waiting for evac.

663
01:02:40,956 --> 01:02:42,891
Evac?

664
01:02:42,892 --> 01:02:44,692
There's no evac coming for you.

665
01:02:44,693 --> 01:02:46,361
End of the road.

666
01:02:46,362 --> 01:02:48,363
They promised.

667
01:02:48,364 --> 01:02:50,368
Who's "they"?

668
01:02:51,333 --> 01:02:53,735
My recruiter.

669
01:02:54,503 --> 01:02:56,473
My CO.

670
01:02:57,806 --> 01:02:59,776
All of 'em.

671
01:03:00,910 --> 01:03:02,914
What did they promise?

672
01:03:03,212 --> 01:03:06,748
To know I was fighting for
something that mattered.

673
01:03:06,749 --> 01:03:08,821
I was doing good.

674
01:03:10,052 --> 01:03:12,056
Maybe you were.

675
01:03:13,756 --> 01:03:15,723
No.

676
01:03:15,724 --> 01:03:17,728
I wasn't.

677
01:04:05,608 --> 01:04:08,510
(GRUNTING)

678
01:04:10,112 --> 01:04:12,046
Your old man was out there with me

679
01:04:12,047 --> 01:04:15,791
and it did not do me any good
having him watch my six.

680
01:04:28,897 --> 01:04:30,832
Ah, ah, ah.

681
01:04:31,500 --> 01:04:34,243
Say hi to your old man
when you see him.

682
01:04:34,503 --> 01:04:36,738
- My father's dead.
- Is he?

683
01:04:36,739 --> 01:04:40,586
- Well, you killed him.
- Well, I thought I did, but he's here.

684
01:04:41,076 --> 01:04:43,080
- Here?
- Yep.

685
01:04:43,479 --> 01:04:46,154
He's on the scent,

686
01:04:46,582 --> 01:04:49,086
doing what he does best.

687
01:04:52,788 --> 01:04:57,258
Now, I want you to
do a favor for me.

688
01:04:57,259 --> 01:05:01,829
Tell your old man and the
Colonel that I'm coming for 'em.

689
01:05:01,830 --> 01:05:03,765
(CLICKS)

690
01:05:03,832 --> 01:05:05,836
Don't you hate that?

691
01:05:13,942 --> 01:05:16,549
(DISTORTED SPEECH)

692
01:05:33,562 --> 01:05:37,068
- Let's talk.
- You cannot torture me.

693
01:05:37,466 --> 01:05:40,468
Really? Who says?

694
01:05:40,469 --> 01:05:42,780
Your government says.

695
01:05:47,843 --> 01:05:51,986
I can do what the fuck
I like. I'm in Syria.

696
01:05:52,981 --> 01:05:56,718
You think my government sent
me here to follow the rules?

697
01:05:56,719 --> 01:06:00,688
They sent me here to take
down creeps like you.

698
01:06:00,689 --> 01:06:05,259
They don't ask me how
I do it and I don't tell.

699
01:06:05,260 --> 01:06:07,230
(LAUGHS)

700
01:06:07,262 --> 01:06:09,800
Don't ask, don't tell.

701
01:06:10,399 --> 01:06:12,573
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

702
01:06:16,105 --> 01:06:17,872
- Excuse me.
- (BEEPS)

703
01:06:17,873 --> 01:06:20,108
Won't be long.

704
01:06:20,109 --> 01:06:21,509
Colonel.

705
01:06:21,510 --> 01:06:24,078
- Sharpe's dead?
<i>- Yes, he is.</i>

706
01:06:24,079 --> 01:06:26,047
And I got to find out
from a third party?

707
01:06:26,048 --> 01:06:27,448
We've been busy.

708
01:06:27,449 --> 01:06:30,454
Understood. We got to
get this done, Major.

709
01:06:31,687 --> 01:06:33,388
Listen, Colonel, I know
this thing has gone

710
01:06:33,389 --> 01:06:37,463
a bit sideways and I'm
willing to wear that,

711
01:06:37,960 --> 01:06:40,561
but I've got a piece of business
right in front of me now.

712
01:06:40,562 --> 01:06:41,929
What kind of business?

713
01:06:41,930 --> 01:06:46,107
A captive hostile.
How far can I take this?

714
01:06:46,602 --> 01:06:51,205
No limits. Major, don't let
this ax come to my door.

715
01:06:51,206 --> 01:06:53,483
Roger that.

716
01:06:59,448 --> 01:07:02,123
Now where were we?

717
01:07:03,285 --> 01:07:05,220
(SCREAMS)

718
01:07:06,555 --> 01:07:10,698
Now you talk or you die.

719
01:07:10,759 --> 01:07:12,694
(GROANS)

720
01:07:39,788 --> 01:07:42,065
He's gone.

721
01:07:45,994 --> 01:07:48,032
Dad?

722
01:07:48,497 --> 01:07:50,501
Hello, son.

723
01:08:02,478 --> 01:08:05,980
BECKETT: You need to
rendezvous with the team.

724
01:08:05,981 --> 01:08:09,016
BRANDON: You're a hard man to
find, Master Gunnery Sergeant.

725
01:08:09,017 --> 01:08:11,089
BECKETT: Yeah.

726
01:08:11,620 --> 01:08:15,729
I guess that's the idea.
Scout Sniper and all.

727
01:08:46,522 --> 01:08:47,722
It's me.

728
01:08:47,723 --> 01:08:49,658
Easy, Master Guns.

729
01:08:57,366 --> 01:08:59,100
(SHIP HORN BLOWING)

730
01:08:59,101 --> 01:09:01,105
Still leaving the unit?

731
01:09:01,236 --> 01:09:03,513
I don't know.

732
01:09:04,339 --> 01:09:07,742
You're fighting a good war, Brandon.

733
01:09:07,743 --> 01:09:09,781
We're on the right side of it.

734
01:09:10,012 --> 01:09:14,215
Yeah. Well, maybe I just
joined for the wrong reasons.

735
01:09:14,216 --> 01:09:16,356
You should go talk to him.

736
01:09:22,925 --> 01:09:25,393
(SCOFFS) I don't even know him.

737
01:09:25,394 --> 01:09:30,333
And the next thing I knew, I became
him. I'm not sure where to begin.

738
01:09:31,567 --> 01:09:34,735
"Where the fuck you
been my whole life?"

739
01:09:34,736 --> 01:09:37,115
Start there.

740
01:09:39,708 --> 01:09:42,315
Don't let this moment pass you.

741
01:10:05,834 --> 01:10:07,804
(CLEARS THROAT)

742
01:10:08,904 --> 01:10:13,808
Look here, I know there's some
questions you want to ask me, Gunny.

743
01:10:13,809 --> 01:10:17,979
And I'm afraid you're not
gonna like the answers.

744
01:10:17,980 --> 01:10:21,515
A sniper is just not a father.

745
01:10:21,516 --> 01:10:25,090
I walked. It happened.

746
01:10:25,587 --> 01:10:30,594
Should I go on or can we skip
this sad story with all its tears?

747
01:10:34,529 --> 01:10:38,706
Let's skip it. Let's
talk about the mission.

748
01:10:39,768 --> 01:10:41,840
Okay.

749
01:10:42,504 --> 01:10:45,543
- Simpson, the assassin...
- BIDWELL: Simpson's working alone.

750
01:10:46,708 --> 01:10:48,848
Major?

751
01:10:49,277 --> 01:10:50,878
No, he was never with them.

752
01:10:50,879 --> 01:10:52,883
How do you know that?

753
01:10:53,649 --> 01:10:56,617
Well, my guy turned out
to be quite talkative.

754
01:10:56,618 --> 01:10:58,686
- Huh.
- So how do we catch him?

755
01:10:58,687 --> 01:11:00,521
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

756
01:11:00,522 --> 01:11:02,523
Question.

757
01:11:02,524 --> 01:11:04,525
Who sent all of you out here?

758
01:11:04,526 --> 01:11:06,127
Who else?

759
01:11:06,128 --> 01:11:08,195
The last thing Simpson
said to me was

760
01:11:08,196 --> 01:11:10,398
that he was gunning for
you and the Colonel.

761
01:11:10,399 --> 01:11:11,966
Sounds like a trap to me.

762
01:11:11,967 --> 01:11:14,608
Or a misdirection.

763
01:11:14,636 --> 01:11:17,872
Maybe he wants us to lead him there.

764
01:11:17,873 --> 01:11:20,081
The Colonel's in Santorini.

765
01:11:21,743 --> 01:11:24,045
In Greece?

766
01:11:24,046 --> 01:11:26,084
That's his new pivot point?

767
01:11:26,415 --> 01:11:28,487
Nice.

768
01:11:29,885 --> 01:11:33,766
Well, looks like we'll
need a cruise ship.

769
01:11:49,838 --> 01:11:52,615
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

770
01:12:03,618 --> 01:12:04,785
Him?

771
01:12:04,786 --> 01:12:07,121
He's the only one we didn't
take on the mission.

772
01:12:07,122 --> 01:12:11,526
Welcome to the shit, Reese.
All right, let's load up.

773
01:12:17,365 --> 01:12:20,506
Reese, we good?

774
01:12:20,869 --> 01:12:22,570
I'm good.

775
01:12:22,571 --> 01:12:24,882
Unless you wanna go again?

776
01:12:25,207 --> 01:12:28,144
Not really. But we can.

777
01:12:29,144 --> 01:12:32,786
Let's not. You kicked
my ass the first time.

778
01:12:43,091 --> 01:12:44,825
Are these scanners operational?

779
01:12:44,826 --> 01:12:46,327
They should be.

780
01:12:46,328 --> 01:12:47,595
What do you got in mind?

781
01:12:47,596 --> 01:12:51,298
You said this shooter uses a
remote control firing platform.

782
01:12:51,299 --> 01:12:54,101
Remote-firing systems are
linked in to cell signals.

783
01:12:54,102 --> 01:12:56,270
With a cell-tuned scanner,
I could pinpoint

784
01:12:56,271 --> 01:12:59,208
the exact location of
his firing platform.

785
01:13:01,476 --> 01:13:03,480
Get on that.

786
01:13:05,781 --> 01:13:08,354
So, who is this guy anyway?

787
01:13:08,416 --> 01:13:09,950
He's working for someone.

788
01:13:09,951 --> 01:13:11,652
Or he's crazy.

789
01:13:11,653 --> 01:13:13,657
Or both.

790
01:13:17,959 --> 01:13:20,998
I hunted this kid once.

791
01:13:21,596 --> 01:13:24,198
He did the hero side of Afghanistan

792
01:13:24,199 --> 01:13:26,300
from the Fifth Stryker Brigade.

793
01:13:26,301 --> 01:13:29,238
A 15-month deployment in
the Helmand River Valley.

794
01:13:29,437 --> 01:13:33,250
Heavy action, really heavy.

795
01:13:34,042 --> 01:13:38,913
You know, he was a good Marine,

796
01:13:39,347 --> 01:13:42,386
but it got to his soul.

797
01:13:43,351 --> 01:13:46,527
Messed him up really good.

798
01:13:47,222 --> 01:13:53,128
The psychs tagged him with PTSD,
but they didn't discharge him.

799
01:13:53,562 --> 01:13:56,874
They didn't really treat him either.

800
01:13:58,033 --> 01:14:01,812
For three months he wandered
the base with a weapon.

801
01:14:03,038 --> 01:14:07,041
January first,
he went into his hooch,

802
01:14:07,042 --> 01:14:11,549
grabbed his weapon and he
shot up a New Year's Party.

803
01:14:11,746 --> 01:14:15,957
Then he trekked up to
Yosemite National Forest.

804
01:14:16,184 --> 01:14:20,065
No food, no shelter,

805
01:14:21,089 --> 01:14:23,900
temperatures dropping
below freezing.

806
01:14:25,160 --> 01:14:31,066
When we finally spotted him, he was
up the mountain above the snow line.

807
01:14:33,668 --> 01:14:39,745
Just sitting there, staring
into dawn's early light.

808
01:14:42,878 --> 01:14:45,758
And then he ate his gun.

809
01:14:46,615 --> 01:14:49,290
If Simpson's broken,

810
01:14:49,851 --> 01:14:52,753
he makes a perfect
puppet for the Colonel.

811
01:14:52,754 --> 01:14:54,758
What? You think he's in on this?

812
01:14:55,624 --> 01:14:58,128
I sure hope to God he's not.

813
01:15:53,415 --> 01:15:55,385
You don't drink coffee?

814
01:15:56,751 --> 01:15:58,721
Not much.

815
01:15:58,820 --> 01:16:00,755
No bad habits?

816
01:16:01,022 --> 01:16:03,196
I like cars.

817
01:16:03,858 --> 01:16:05,626
That's a bad habit?

818
01:16:05,627 --> 01:16:07,597
It is if they're expensive.

819
01:16:08,163 --> 01:16:10,371
How about you?

820
01:16:14,169 --> 01:16:16,241
I like to fish.

821
01:16:18,707 --> 01:16:21,848
Well, maybe we'll
cast a line someday.

822
01:16:25,347 --> 01:16:27,385
- Hey, Dad?
- Yeah.

823
01:16:29,617 --> 01:16:32,337
Might want to get square,
if you're gonna go see a colonel.

824
01:16:39,294 --> 01:16:41,229
Right.

825
01:16:47,202 --> 01:16:48,902
If you get this Simpson
in your sights,

826
01:16:48,903 --> 01:16:50,804
you put some hot lead into him.

827
01:16:50,805 --> 01:16:52,877
One shot, one kill.

828
01:16:52,974 --> 01:16:54,909
Yes, sir.

829
01:16:55,043 --> 01:16:56,978
Brandon?

830
01:17:01,916 --> 01:17:03,886
You hold my weapon.

831
01:17:05,153 --> 01:17:07,088
Master Guns.

832
01:18:14,322 --> 01:18:16,997
(CHATTERING)

833
01:18:29,170 --> 01:18:31,640
(THE COLONEL CHUCKLES)

834
01:18:33,141 --> 01:18:36,180
Excuse me, sir.
You have a phone call.

835
01:18:37,145 --> 01:18:39,353
Excuse me, please.

836
01:18:39,914 --> 01:18:41,315
Yes, who's this?

837
01:18:41,316 --> 01:18:44,389
Former Master Gunnery
Sergeant Thomas Beckett, sir.

838
01:18:44,752 --> 01:18:46,353
Beckett?

839
01:18:46,354 --> 01:18:47,488
Thought you were dead.

840
01:18:47,489 --> 01:18:51,125
You mean you heard I was dead,
but I'm betting you didn't believe it.

841
01:18:51,126 --> 01:18:52,426
That's true.

842
01:18:52,427 --> 01:18:53,527
Where are you?

843
01:18:53,528 --> 01:18:54,962
<i>On my way to see you.</i>

844
01:18:54,963 --> 01:18:56,898
Are you close?

845
01:18:57,098 --> 01:18:58,198
Very.

846
01:18:58,199 --> 01:19:00,167
<i>Should I send someone?</i>

847
01:19:00,168 --> 01:19:01,869
No, I'll cab it.

848
01:19:01,870 --> 01:19:03,804
1322 Thira Drive.

849
01:19:03,805 --> 01:19:06,013
<i>I know, over.</i>

850
01:19:31,866 --> 01:19:34,370
<i>BIDWELL:
Say your positions, everybody.</i>

851
01:20:44,205 --> 01:20:46,240
BIDWELL:
Keep your eyes on the perimeter.

852
01:20:46,241 --> 01:20:48,176
Scanning.

853
01:20:50,945 --> 01:20:54,155
If Simpson's here, I want him dead.

854
01:22:08,423 --> 01:22:11,394
Wow. Nice office.

855
01:22:11,559 --> 01:22:14,769
You certainly made a
deal with the devil, sir.

856
01:22:15,496 --> 01:22:17,230
This is a breach of protocol.

857
01:22:17,231 --> 01:22:19,576
You didn't have to see me, Colonel.

858
01:22:20,902 --> 01:22:24,538
You call me up from the grave
and expect me not to respond?

859
01:22:24,539 --> 01:22:25,906
Do you know who I have up there?

860
01:22:25,907 --> 01:22:27,979
Yeah.

861
01:22:28,276 --> 01:22:29,443
The, uh...

862
01:22:29,444 --> 01:22:32,346
The US Attorney
General, Phil Daniels,

863
01:22:32,347 --> 01:22:35,955
the esteemed Senator
from North Dakota,

864
01:22:37,552 --> 01:22:39,286
and the Syrian Rebel Forces.

865
01:22:39,287 --> 01:22:42,827
And from the looks of it,
a couple of <i>Playboy</i> Bunnies.

866
01:22:44,292 --> 01:22:48,173
Well, we don't all wear a
ghillie suit and creep around.

867
01:22:48,596 --> 01:22:50,531
Question.

868
01:22:50,732 --> 01:22:52,933
Did you send an assassin to track me

869
01:22:52,934 --> 01:22:55,068
and the other members
of Mission Sentinel?

870
01:22:55,069 --> 01:22:58,372
If I sent a kill squad for you,

871
01:22:58,373 --> 01:23:01,275
you would not be here
having this conversation.

872
01:23:01,442 --> 01:23:04,822
Damn, Thomas, we go back a long way.

873
01:23:06,748 --> 01:23:08,956
Yeah, yep.

874
01:23:09,217 --> 01:23:11,084
- Twenty-five years.
- That's right.

875
01:23:11,085 --> 01:23:13,453
So, if you think I'm
gonna stand here

876
01:23:13,454 --> 01:23:15,455
and let you point your
finger in my face,

877
01:23:15,456 --> 01:23:16,990
you can go to straight
to hell, Beckett.

878
01:23:16,991 --> 01:23:18,392
Well, then tell me what's happening.

879
01:23:18,393 --> 01:23:21,495
What's happening is David Simpson.

880
01:23:21,496 --> 01:23:24,876
He's been in the game too
long and he had a meltdown.

881
01:23:26,234 --> 01:23:29,336
And let me tell you something,
there is no conspiracy here.

882
01:23:29,337 --> 01:23:31,375
I'm telling you what I know.

883
01:23:35,143 --> 01:23:38,812
Well, tell me something, Colonel,

884
01:23:38,813 --> 01:23:43,388
does this, um, black-on-black
work ever wear you out?

885
01:23:45,153 --> 01:23:50,024
Yeah, it does,
when I think about it.

886
01:23:51,259 --> 01:23:54,366
- How's Brandon?
- Ah...

887
01:23:55,196 --> 01:23:58,042
Sins of the father, I guess.

888
01:24:02,003 --> 01:24:04,771
You've given up a lot for
your country, Master Guns.

889
01:24:04,772 --> 01:24:07,845
Maybe it's time you
consider a change of venue.

890
01:24:08,676 --> 01:24:10,944
You can have any job you want.

891
01:24:10,945 --> 01:24:14,883
Because by far, you are the
best Marine I have ever known.

892
01:24:15,516 --> 01:24:17,050
(WHIRRING)

893
01:24:17,051 --> 01:24:19,021
(SCREAMING)

894
01:24:19,320 --> 01:24:20,554
Gunshot came from my six.

895
01:24:20,555 --> 01:24:22,866
<i>BIDWELL: Find him and shut him down.</i>

896
01:24:23,458 --> 01:24:24,791
Get me a location, Malik.

897
01:24:24,792 --> 01:24:25,892
- (BEEPING)
- I'm on it.

898
01:24:25,893 --> 01:24:29,603
God damn it, Thomas!
You've led him right to me.

899
01:24:39,674 --> 01:24:41,609
(GRUNTS)

900
01:24:42,009 --> 01:24:45,219
If he's using a remote
platform, I'm not seeing it.

901
01:24:53,187 --> 01:24:56,260
Got him, 2,600 meters out.

902
01:25:00,561 --> 01:25:03,270
(WHIRRING)

903
01:25:03,364 --> 01:25:06,107
<i>BIDWELL: Missed, too far down range.</i>

904
01:25:09,103 --> 01:25:12,449
He's on the move, headed
southbound on the ridge-line.

905
01:25:13,007 --> 01:25:15,409
Roger that, on my way.

906
01:25:41,235 --> 01:25:42,903
REESE: I've got a visual on him.

907
01:25:42,904 --> 01:25:44,804
BIDWELL:
If you have a shot, take it.

908
01:25:44,805 --> 01:25:48,379
<i>REESE: That's a negative, I'm in
pursuit on the southbound trail.</i>

909
01:26:37,658 --> 01:26:39,593
Fuck.

910
01:26:40,261 --> 01:26:41,361
Put the weapon down.

911
01:26:41,362 --> 01:26:43,332
Don't do it!

912
01:26:45,366 --> 01:26:48,041
Don't do it.

913
01:26:51,939 --> 01:26:54,975
Vintage Remington 308.

914
01:26:54,976 --> 01:26:56,977
Not the best for accuracy.

915
01:26:56,978 --> 01:26:59,880
Blow his fucking head off, Sarge!

916
01:27:00,548 --> 01:27:02,518
(BRANDON FIRES)

917
01:27:29,143 --> 01:27:31,078
(BEEPING)

918
01:27:33,247 --> 01:27:35,649
(BEEPS AND WHIRS)

919
01:27:39,720 --> 01:27:41,792
Talk to me, Malik.

920
01:27:41,822 --> 01:27:43,826
I'm getting a weak signal.

921
01:28:06,447 --> 01:28:08,782
There's no signal with
a remote, Brandon.

922
01:28:08,783 --> 01:28:10,617
I've got the eastern side
of the ruins covered.

923
01:28:10,618 --> 01:28:11,851
<i>BRANDON: Roger that.</i>

924
01:28:11,852 --> 01:28:14,421
I'm gonna draw him out.
Watch for movement.

925
01:28:14,422 --> 01:28:16,056
I'm on the scope, kid.

926
01:28:16,057 --> 01:28:19,028
Waiting to get a vector
on his position.

927
01:28:31,138 --> 01:28:33,740
Give it up, Simpson! You're done!

928
01:28:33,741 --> 01:28:36,052
This ends badly for you!

929
01:28:42,116 --> 01:28:43,983
Any reading on that
frequency yet, Malik?

930
01:28:43,984 --> 01:28:45,552
I got it.

931
01:28:45,553 --> 01:28:48,626
1,200 meters to the west,
headed there now.

932
01:29:11,245 --> 01:29:13,385
Isn't this fun?

933
01:29:13,748 --> 01:29:16,218
Let's get to it, Junior!

934
01:29:25,192 --> 01:29:27,503
<i>I missed. He's still in play.</i>

935
01:29:30,364 --> 01:29:34,434
Remote platform's not here.
He must have scrambled the signal.

936
01:29:34,435 --> 01:29:36,102
I'm on my way down.

937
01:29:36,103 --> 01:29:38,038
(BEEPING)

938
01:29:41,842 --> 01:29:44,244
What happened to you, Simpson?

939
01:29:44,879 --> 01:29:46,780
They lied!

940
01:29:46,781 --> 01:29:48,648
I read the reports.

941
01:29:48,649 --> 01:29:51,351
No one ordered you to
fire on your own team.

942
01:29:51,352 --> 01:29:54,554
It was an accident, friendly fire.

943
01:29:54,555 --> 01:29:56,523
It wasn't an accident.

944
01:29:56,524 --> 01:29:58,458
I was under orders.

945
01:29:58,459 --> 01:30:00,861
- They made me do it.
- (BEEPING)

946
01:30:02,563 --> 01:30:04,806
It was not my fault!

947
01:30:16,010 --> 01:30:17,945
(CLICKS)

948
01:30:24,718 --> 01:30:26,653
(BEEPING)

949
01:30:32,259 --> 01:30:35,002
Welcome to my kill zone, Junior.

950
01:30:45,105 --> 01:30:47,075
(YELLING)

951
01:30:59,587 --> 01:31:01,522
Come on!

952
01:31:15,236 --> 01:31:17,171
Toss it now.

953
01:31:19,740 --> 01:31:21,675
Get the fuck up.

954
01:31:26,380 --> 01:31:28,623
You're enjoying this, aren't you?

955
01:31:31,619 --> 01:31:33,052
Why shouldn't I?

956
01:31:33,053 --> 01:31:35,321
This is my last hurrah.

957
01:31:35,322 --> 01:31:37,860
(BEEPS AND POWERS DOWN)

958
01:31:40,594 --> 01:31:43,062
The field sniper is a dinosaur.

959
01:31:43,063 --> 01:31:47,069
